The paper discusses improving entity resolution in web search, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and databases (DB). The use of socio-economic properties of online user behavior suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are subfields of artificial intelligence (AI) and computational linguistics (CL).
